item.title: Error In My Castle Wars Waiting Room Timer
item.dc:creator: @Godsent Godsent
item.description:
@Godsent wrote:

[quote=“Teh Moose, post:1, topic:245006”]Note: This is a very basic test so don’t ask why it teles you where it does lol

Ok, I’m using this to tele you to castle wars after 1 minute in waiting room…
public int cwwr = 120; // castle wars waiting room, 2 = 1 sec, 120 = 1 min, 3600 = 30 min.
process() {
cwwr-=1;

if(cwwr == 0) { //duration = the time on cwwr should be ended
teleportToX = 2404;
teleportToY = 3101;
cwwr = 120;
} else {
teleportToX = 2423;
teleportToY = 9529;
}
}
And I get this error…

client.java:26: invalid method declaration; return type required
process() {
^
1 error
Files Compiled Successfully!
Press any key to continue . . .

Any Ideas or help?[/quote]
You have 2 processes (Looks like it to me) and you didn’t add what it should be.

public int cwwr = 120; // castle wars waiting room, 2 = 1 sec, 120 = 1 min, 3600 = 30 min. [b]public boolean[/b] process() { cwwr-=1;

if(cwwr == 0) { //duration = the time on cwwr should be ended
teleportToX = 2404;
teleportToY = 3101;
cwwr = 120;
} else {
teleportToX = 2423;
teleportToY = 9529;
}
}

If that doesn’t work, search for

boolean process

And add this under the bracket:

[code]
cwwr-=1;

if(cwwr == 0) { //duration = the time on cwwr should be ended
teleportToX = 2404;
teleportToY = 3101;
cwwr = 120;
} else {
teleportToX = 2423;
teleportToY = 9529;
}
}[/code]
